CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1956, page 21, reads: "8. Winners of the Clabber Girl cake-baking contest, left to right: Mrs. Lillie Harris, first prize; Mrs. Rossie Thompson, second prize; Mrs. E.K. Johnson, third prize; Mrs. Ida Rivers, fourth prize; Mrs. Clifton Pope, fifth prize, and MRs. Beatrice Hall, honorable mention"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Lillie Harris, Rossie Thompson, Mrs. E.K. Johnson, Ida Rivers, Mrs. Clifton Pope, and Beatrice Hall holding cakes, posed in front of cooking demonstration area at Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair in the Syria Mosque
